       <article class="post-276 page type-page status-publish hentry" id="post-276">
        <header class="entry-header">
         <h1 class="entry-title">
          WELCOME
         </h1>
        </header>
        <!-- .entry-header -->
        <div class="entry-content">
         <p>
          <a href="https://elt.blogs.rice.edu/files/2015/08/group-photo-1al54il.jpg">
           <img alt="" class="alignnone wp-image-526" height="364" sizes="(max-width: 486px) 100vw, 486px" src="https://elt.blogs.rice.edu/files/2015/08/group-photo-1al54il-300x225.jpg" srcset="http://elt.rice.edu/files/2015/08/group-photo-1al54il-300x225.jpg 300w, http://elt.rice.edu/files/2015/08/group-photo-1al54il-768x576.jpg 768w, http://elt.rice.edu/files/2015/08/group-photo-1al54il-1024x768.jpg 1024w" width="486"/>
          </a>
         </p>
         <p>
          Thomas Research Group is focused on the development of novel polymers and polymer-based composite materials with unusual optical, mechanical, and electronic properties. The research is very interdisciplinary with members having backgrounds in materials science, chemistry, physics and mechanical engineering. The main areas of current interest include photonics, phononics, mechanical properties of complex materials, and polymer structure and morphology.
         </p>
        </div>
        <!-- .entry-content -->
       </article>
